### Apply Instance-Wide Theming with CSS Color Tokens

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/self-hosting/guides/white-labeling/introduction.mdx

Customize the overall look and feel of your Cal.com instance by modifying the hex color codes defined as color tokens in the `globals.css` file. This ensures a consistent brand identity across the application.

```css
/* Modify hex codes against color tokens */
:root {
  --color-primary: #yourPrimaryColor;
  --color-secondary: #yourSecondaryColor;
  /* ... other color tokens */
}
```

